    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Neil L. Rudenstine, the 26th president of Harvard University -- and only the sixth appointed since the Civil War -- plans to step down next spring after a decade leading the nation's oldest and most prestigious university.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Neil L. Rudenstine, the 26th president of Harvard University -- and only the sixth appointed since the Civil War -- plans to step down next spring after a decade leading the nation's oldest and most prestigious university.</p>
        <p>Mr. Rudenstine, who took a three-month leave because of exhaustion in 1994, said he is not too tired to continue. Rather, having completed a $2.6 billion capital campaign -- the largest ever in higher education -- he thinks it is time for a new regime to plan for the next round of fund-raising.</p>
        <p>JODI WILGOREN</p>
      </block>
